<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,1934,2068]" lastBlockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,201,1934,1960]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vellozo" authorityYear="1831" box="[237,423,1934,1960]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fistulosa">
<emphasis box="[237,423,1934,1960]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Lobelia fistulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was validly published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vellozo, J. M. da C." box="[708,874,1934,1960]" firstAuthor="Vellozo" journalOrPublisher="Senefelder, Paris" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" pagination="157" refId="ref8162" refString="Vellozo, J. M. da C. (1831) (&quot; 1827 &quot;) Florae Fluminensis icones, vol. 8. Senefelder, Paris. t. 157." title="Florae Fluminensis icones, vol. 8" type="book" year="1831">Vellozo (1831)</bibRefCitation>
as a single analytical plate in his 
<emphasis box="[1238,1444,1934,1960]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Flora Fluminensis</emphasis>
, with the full description published only fifty years later (
<bibRefCitation author="Vellozo, J. M. da C." box="[817,977,1970,1996]" firstAuthor="Vellozo" journalOrPublisher="Archivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 461" part="5" refId="ref8195" refString="Vellozo, J. M. da C. (1881) Florae Fluminensis .... Archivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro 5: 1 - 461." title="Florae Fluminensis ..." type="journal article" year="1881">Vellozo 1881</bibRefCitation>
). Since Vellozo’s original collection has disappeared (
<bibRefCitation author="Bocage, J. V. B." bookContentInfo="96 pp." box="[284,435,2006,2032]" firstAuthor="Bocage" journalOrPublisher="Museu de Lisboa, Lisboa" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" refId="ref6637" refString="Bocage, J. V. B. (1862) Ilustracoes praticas sobre o modo de colligir, preparar e remeter produtos zoologicos para o Museu de Lisboa. Museu de Lisboa, Lisboa, 96 pp." title="Ilustracoes praticas sobre o modo de colligir, preparar e remeter produtos zoologicos para o Museu de Lisboa" type="book" year="1862">Bocage 1862</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hamy, E. T." bookContentInfo="66 pp." box="[446,580,2006,2032]" firstAuthor="Hamy" journalOrPublisher="Masson, Paris" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" refId="ref6994" refString="Hamy, E. T. (1908) La Mission d ' Etienne Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire en Espagne et en Portugal (1808). Histoire et documents. Masson, Paris, 66 pp." title="La Mission d ' Etienne Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire en Espagne et en Portugal (1808). Histoire et documents" type="book" year="1908">Hamy 1908</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carauta, J. P. P." box="[591,743,2006,2032]" firstAuthor="Carauta" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" pagination="281 - 284" part="22" refId="ref6776" refString="Carauta, J. P. P. (1973) The text of Vellozo's Flora Fluminensis and the effective date of publication. Taxon 22: 281 - 284. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1218138" title="The text of Vellozo's Flora Fluminensis and the effective date of publication" type="journal article" year="1973">Carauta 1973</bibRefCitation>
), the only original material eligible for a 
<typeStatus box="[1202,1305,2006,2032]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">lectotype</typeStatus>
selection are the original iconographs. We selected the original plate kept at the manuscript section of the Arquivo Nacional da Torre do Tombo in 
<collectingRegion box="[287,365,158,184]" country="Portugal" name="Lisboa" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lisbon</collectingRegion>
as its 
<typeStatus box="[438,544,158,184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Along with another original plate kept at Biblioteca Nacional in 
<collectingRegion box="[1281,1448,158,184]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, it is the only available material while Vellozo was still alive. It is also slightly more detailed than the plate kept at the Biblioteca Nacional in 
<collectingRegion box="[395,557,230,256]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and its published version of 1831.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Vellozo’s plate (
<bibRefCitation author="Vellozo, J. M. da C." box="[370,523,266,292]" firstAuthor="Vellozo" journalOrPublisher="Senefelder, Paris" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="157" refId="ref8162" refString="Vellozo, J. M. da C. (1831) (&quot; 1827 &quot;) Florae Fluminensis icones, vol. 8. Senefelder, Paris. t. 157." title="Florae Fluminensis icones, vol. 8" type="book" year="1831">
Vellozo 
<date box="[465,523,266,292]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1831-05-08">1831</date>
</bibRefCitation>
, v. 8: t. 157) perfectly details the growth form, leaf, bracts and flower morphology characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vellozo" authorityYear="1831" box="[327,453,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fistulosa">
<emphasis box="[327,453,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L. fistulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The main character allowing for the recognition of the species in the illustration is its large, erect, and conspicuous lanceolate bracts covering the pedicels. The locality description provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vellozo, J. M. da C." firstAuthor="Vellozo" journalOrPublisher="Archivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 461" part="5" refId="ref8195" refString="Vellozo, J. M. da C. (1881) Florae Fluminensis .... Archivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro 5: 1 - 461." title="Florae Fluminensis ..." type="journal article" year="1881">Vellozo (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, “habitat medit. Loca humentia ad ripas rivulorum”, corresponds to the municipality of 
<collectingCountry box="[1227,1303,374,400]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Cunha</collectingCountry>
, state of São Paulo (
<bibRefCitation author="Pastore, J. F. B. &amp; Mota, M. &amp; de Menezes, H. F. &amp; Trovo, M." box="[214,429,410,436]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Pastore" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="1078 - 1095" part="70" refId="ref7634" refString="Pastore, J. F. B., Mota, M., de Menezes, H. F. &amp; Trovo, M. (2021) Vellozo's Florae Fluminensis: A new assessment of the Sao Paulo part of his collecting itinerary, its vegetation, and species list. Taxon 70: 1078 - 1095. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12509" title="Vellozo's Florae Fluminensis: A new assessment of the Sao Paulo part of his collecting itinerary, its vegetation, and species list" type="journal article" year="2021">
Pastore 
<emphasis box="[306,362,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chamisso" authorityYear="1833" box="[189,409,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uranocoma">
<emphasis box="[189,409,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lobelia uranocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chamisso, A." box="[614,805,446,472]" firstAuthor="Chamisso" journalOrPublisher="Linnaea" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="201 - 223" part="8" refId="ref6817" refString="Chamisso, A. (1833) De plantis in expeditione speculatoria Romanzoffiana et in herbariis Regiis observatis dicere pergitur: Lobeliaceae. Linnaea 8 (3): 201 - 223." title="De plantis in expeditione speculatoria Romanzoffiana et in herbariis Regiis observatis dicere pergitur: Lobeliaceae" type="journal article" year="1833">Chamisso (1833)</bibRefCitation>
based on a specimen housed at B and collected by Sellow in 
<collectingCountry box="[164,236,482,508]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. That specimen was unfortunately lost during the World War II, but a photo available from the Field Museum negatives collection shows a specimen with a label by Chamisso containing the species identification, along with details of the species protologue, collector, and the location in “Brasilia”. Our search for duplicates of this collection led to two sheets housed at M, identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chamisso" authorityYear="1833" box="[501,657,591,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uranocoma">
<emphasis box="[501,657,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L. uranocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and collected by Sellow in 
<collectingCountry box="[961,1033,590,616]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The specimen M0185354, composed only of some leaves and a basal part of the stem, bears an original loan label from B in Chamisso’s handwriting. The specimen M0185353, composed of an inflorescence and distal part of the stem, bears an M label with the same information copied in someone else’s hand. In accordance with Art. 8.2 of ICN (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J." box="[1021,1182,698,724]" firstAuthor="McNeill" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="1112 - 1113" part="63" refId="ref7546" refString="McNeill, J. (2014) Holotype specimens and type citations: General issues. Taxon 63: 1112 - 1113. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 635.7" title="Holotype specimens and type citations: General issues" type="journal article" year="2014">McNeill 2014</bibRefCitation>
), the most parsimonious interpretation of both sheets with the Chamisso analysis is that they represent a single collection sent by B to M.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kanitz" authorityYear="1878" box="[189,581,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Haynaldia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="organensis" variety="insignis">
<emphasis box="[189,437,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Haynaldia organensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[494,581,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanitz, A." box="[791,948,770,796]" editor="Martius, C. F. P. von" firstAuthor="Kanitz" journalOrPublisher="Frid. Fleischer, Leipzig" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="130 - 187" refId="ref7111" refString="Kanitz, A. (1878) Lobeliaceae. In: Martius, C. F. P. von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 6 (4). Frid. Fleischer, Leipzig, pp. 130 - 187." title="Lobeliaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 6 (4)" year="1878">Kanitz (1878)</bibRefCitation>
in his revision for 
<emphasis box="[1164,1376,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Flora Brasiliensis.</emphasis>
It was based on 
<emphasis box="[244,396,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lindberg 610</emphasis>
, a specimen with no flowers or leaves, thus being the reason, as argued by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanitz, A." box="[1257,1416,806,832]" editor="Martius, C. F. P. von" firstAuthor="Kanitz" journalOrPublisher="Frid. Fleischer, Leipzig" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="130 - 187" refId="ref7111" refString="Kanitz, A. (1878) Lobeliaceae. In: Martius, C. F. P. von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 6 (4). Frid. Fleischer, Leipzig, pp. 130 - 187." title="Lobeliaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 6 (4)" year="1878">Kanitz (1878)</bibRefCitation>
, to describe the taxon as a variety and not as a separate species. The species is currently considered in the synonymy to 
<taxonomicName box="[136,350,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="organensis">
<emphasis box="[136,350,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lobelia organensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation accessDate="invalid" author="Rollim, I. M. &amp; Coelho, G. P. &amp; Trovo, M. &amp; Miotto, S. T. S." box="[364,574,878,905]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rollim" journalOrPublisher="Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" publicationUrl="http://floradobrasil.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB28240" refId="ref7805" refString="Rollim, I. M., Coelho, G. P., Trovo, M. &amp; Miotto, S. T. S. (2020) Campanulaceae. In: Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 28240 (accessed June 2021)." title="Campanulaceae" type="url" volumeTitle="Flora do Brasil 2020" year="2020">
Rollim 
<emphasis box="[451,499,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). However, analyzing the specimen 
<emphasis box="[976,1126,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lindberg 610</emphasis>
, we noticed that its seeds are widely winged, surpassing the seminiferous nucleus, while the seeds of 
<taxonomicName box="[947,1099,915,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="organensis">
<emphasis box="[947,963,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[977,1099,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">organensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have wings proportional to the seminiferous nucleus. Such much larger seeds are more typical of the seeds of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vellozo" authorityYear="1831" box="[1004,1127,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fistulosa">
<emphasis box="[1004,1020,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1032,1127,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">fistulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species with the sympatric distribution to the specimen collected by Lindberg. The variety 
<taxonomicName box="[869,1174,987,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="organensis" variety="insignis">
<emphasis box="[869,1027,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">H. organensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1087,1174,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thus placed here as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vellozo" authorityYear="1831" box="[276,401,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fistulosa">
<emphasis box="[276,401,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L. fistulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
